• Each figure caption must be its own standalone line formatted exactly as: "\"<caption>\" (figure)"; nothing else on that line.
• Do not include quoted strings inside a figure caption.
• Do not include numbers or proper nouns, in figure captions (no years, counts, percentages, named people, organizations, places, or product titles).
• Do not depict numerical charts or diagrams in figure captions; avoid bars, lines, axes, ticks, scales, or data encodings. Prefer icons, illustrations, scenes, or symbolic visuals that support the questions.
• The figure must be rendered in a cartoon or illustrative style and must not contain letters, numerals, words, acronyms, or logos of any kind.
