• If a detail is ambiguous or unsupported, omit it rather than guessing.  
• Indicate roles naturally (title, section header, label, list entry, footnote, URL) and describe placement only in relative terms.

D) Evidence and safety
• Include salient keywords as "\"<text>\" (text)" when literal answers would be awkward (for example, yes/no or long clauses) so answers can be inferred from visuals.  
• Place high-importance keywords near their supporting visuals using only relative terms.  
• Do not contradict the CONTEXT; omit unsupported details. Exclude hateful, sexual, self-harm, or dangerous content. Do not mention URLs or sources.

